##############################
#         TEST51             #
##############################

------------------------------
1. Bremmstrahlung test

A monochromatic electron beam impinges on a slab.
The angular and energetic distributions of emerging photons 
are retrieved. 

------------------------------
2. Experimental set-up
         _
     \  | |  n
   e- \ | |--->
        |_|
        
           z
-------------------->
          

The direction of the incident electrons forms an angle of 45 degrees
with the normal to the slab. The default energy of primary electrons is 70. keV.

All the processes of e-, e+ and photons are active. The cut is 0.5 micrometer.

The default material of the slab is Al. 
Size Z of the slab is: 0.0094 * cm;
Size X, Y of the slab are: 20. * m;

----------------------------
3. Interactive commands

3.1 The user can change interactively the material of the slab with:
/target/setMaterial material

The material of the slab can be: Hydrogen, Beryllium, Oxygen,Aluminium,
Silicon, Iron, Germanium, Gold, Lead.

3.2 The user can change interactively the thickness of the slab along the Z axis with:
/target/setThickness

3.3 The user can change interactively the primary particle, energy, position and direction with the
following commands:
/gun/particle 
/gun/energy
/gun/position -1. -1. -1. m # (position = (-1. m, -1. m ,-1. m)
/gun/direction 0. 0. 1. #( vector = (0., 0., 1.) )

3.4 The user has to define the physics list interactively;

How to activate the standard processes (example in macro_standard.mac):
/physics/addPhysics photon-standard
/physics/addPhysics electron-standard
/physics/addPhysics positron-standard
/run/initialize

How to activate the Low Energy Penelope processes (example in macro_penelope.mac):
/physics/addPhysics photon-penelope
/physics/addPhysics electron-penelope
/physics/addPhysics positron-penelope
/run/initialize

How to activate the Low Energy EEDL processes (example in macro_lowE.mac) with the tsai
angular distribution:
/physics/addPhysics photon-epdl
/physics/addPhysics electron-eedl-tsai
/physics/addPhysics positron-standard
/run/initialize
 
How to activate the Low Energy EEDL processes with the 2BN
angular distribution:
/physics/addPhysics photon-epdl
/physics/addPhysics electron-eedl-2bn
/physics/addPhysics positron-standard
/run/initialize
 
How to activate the Low Energy EEDL processes with the 2BS
angular distribution:
/physics/addPhysics photon-epdl
/physics/addPhysics electron-eedl-2bs
/physics/addPhysics positron-standard
/run/initialize

How to change the cut (threshold of production of secondary particles) interactively:
/physics/cutE 0.5 micrometer
/run/initialize

3. Analysis

The output of the test is test51.hbk;

- Histogram 30: Angular distribution of transmitted photons
- Histogram 40: Energy distribution of transmitted photons
- Histogram 50: Angular distribution of backscattered photons
- Histogram 60: Energy  distribution of backscattered photons
- Nutple 1: energy (kev), angle (deg) of the photons emerging from the slab

4. Set-up 

setup with:
compiler = gcc-3.2.3
G4SYSTEM = linux-g++

The following environment variables need to be set:
G4LEDATA: points to low energy data base - G4EMLOW3.0

setup for analysis with AIDA 3.0/Anaphe 5.0.5 for user with account
on lxplus:

setenv G4ANALYSIS_USE  1
source /afs/cern.ch/sw/lhcxx/share/LHCXX/5.0.5/scripts/setupAnaphe.csh
setenv PATH ${PATH}:/afs/cern.ch/sw/lhcxx/share/LHCXX/5.0.5/scripts/

 Please take a look to the Anaphe/Lizard web page
        http://anaphe.web.cern.ch/anaphe 
 for more info

--------> How to run <----------
1) batch mode
$G4WORKDIR/bin/Linux-g++/test51 file.mac

2) interactive mode
$G4WORKDIR/bin/Linux-g++/test51

run.mac is the default macro executed in interactive mode

